  "texts": [
    "Within this context, Woo et al. [46] proposed the convolutional block attention module (CBAM), which is an effective attention mechanism for CNNs.",
    "The CBAM module includes of a channel attention module (CAM) and a spatial attention module (SAM).",
    "The CAM is focused on the relevant aspects of an input image by exploiting the inter-channel relationships of features.",
    "Two spatial context descriptors are generated in the module using two separate pooling methods (average pooling and max pooling).",
    "Average pooling (AP) is mainly used to gather spatial information, whereas max pooling retains significantly more contextual details pertaining to the object within the image, thereby enabling more precise channel attention."
  ],
